00:15:32,330 --> 00:15:34,530
I suddenly passed out.

266
00:15:35,830 --> 00:15:39,830
Hey, the mouth of the holster of the gun is open!

267
00:15:42,430 --> 00:15:43,430
Don't worry.

268
00:15:43,430 --> 00:15:45,030
Your gun hasn't been taken.

269
00:15:46,230 --> 00:15:49,030
But, why only the gun?

270
00:15:49,030 --> 00:15:52,330
You mean he bought the bullets but didn't own a gun?

271
00:15:52,330 --> 00:15:55,830
I wonder... I can't say for now yet.

272
00:15:55,830 --> 00:15:58,630
But, I more or less have an idea of the case.

273
00:15:59,830 --> 00:16:02,330
Later for the hut.

274
00:16:02,330 --> 00:16:04,530
Let's get everybody together at Mr. Hinohara's house

275
00:16:04,530 --> 00:16:07,430
and solve the mystery, shall we?

276
00:16:11,430 --> 00:16:13,730
A High School Detective from Osaka?

277
00:16:13,730 --> 00:16:15,830
Heiji Hattori?

278
00:16:15,830 --> 00:16:20,030
Are you saying that you're going to solve the mystery

279
00:16:20,030 --> 00:16:25,230
of how Mrs. Kawauchi was stabbed here this morning?

280
00:16:25,230 --> 00:16:27,730
Yes, exactly.

281
00:16:29,230 --> 00:16:31,130
Before that...

282
00:16:31,130 --> 00:16:35,030
If possible, I'd like you to bring along the owner

283
00:16:35,030 --> 00:16:37,530
of the of the mysterious footprints that left

284
00:16:37,530 --> 00:16:39,830
from the backdoor over here with you.

285
00:16:39,830 --> 00:16:42,130
Of course, I brought him along

286
00:16:42,130 --> 00:16:44,430
the owner of the footprints.

287
00:16:46,430 --> 00:16:49,430
Shinichi Kudo, it's you.

288
00:16:49,430 --> 00:16:51,930
What's with the blood on your clothes?

289
00:16:51,930 --> 00:16:53,030
Hey, hey...

290
00:16:53,030 --> 00:16:56,530
Don't tell me that Shinichi's the culprit?

291
00:16:56,530 --> 00:16:59,830
Of all the footprints left in front of this house,

292
00:16:59,830 --> 00:17:02,130
if you exclude the footprints of us

293
00:17:02,130 --> 00:17:05,030
who have an alibi because we were back at the inn

294
00:17:05,030 --> 00:17:06,730
and those of Mrs. Kawauchi,

295
00:17:06,730 --> 00:17:08,730
the only footprints left would be his.

296
00:17:08,730 --> 00:17:10,530
Blood of the victim is splattered on his clothes,

297
00:17:10,530 --> 00:17:12,130
his fingerprints are on the murder weapon...

298
00:17:12,130 --> 00:17:15,230
No matter how you look at it, he's the murderer.

299
00:17:18,530 --> 00:17:20,230
That's true.

300
00:17:20,230 --> 00:17:22,230
Because he is the killer.

301
00:17:32,230 --> 00:17:33,730
In other words,

302
00:17:33,730 --> 00:17:37,330
no trick was used in committing the crime.

303
00:17:37,330 --> 00:17:38,330
What?

304
00:17:39,330 --> 00:17:40,330
Heiji.

305
00:17:41,830 --> 00:17:43,230
What are you up to?

306
00:17:43,230 --> 00:17:44,830
Is this some kind of strategy?

307
00:17:44,830 --> 00:17:46,430
It's not a strategy.

308
00:17:46,430 --> 00:17:49,530
I'm saying that this guy called Mrs. Kawauchi out by phone

309
00:17:49,530 --> 00:17:51,530
and stabbed her.

310
00:17:55,930 --> 00:17:57,430
Hold it.

311
00:17:57,430 --> 00:18:02,630
You insisted this morning that he'd never stab anybody.

312
00:18:02,630 --> 00:18:05,630
I... I was scared.

313
00:18:05,630 --> 00:18:07,530
That newspaper reporter said that

314
00:18:07,530 --> 00:18:12,730
she'd expose the blunder that I made a year ago.

315
00:18:12,730 --> 00:18:16,430
She threatened me saying that she'd shatter the fame

316
00:18:16,430 --> 00:18:19,030
and pride that I'd established up to now.

317
00:18:21,330 --> 00:18:25,430
I didn't know what it was about, but...

318
00:18:25,430 --> 00:18:29,130
I was so scared that I inadvertently...

319
00:18:37,830 --> 00:18:39,830
Who is he?

320
00:18:41,030 --> 00:18:45,030
No. He's not Shinichi.

321
00:18:45,030 --> 00:18:47,830
The Shinichi that I've be waiting for is...

322
00:18:47,830 --> 00:18:49,930
The person that's been filling my heart.

323
00:18:49,930 --> 00:18:52,230
The Shinichi that I've been longing for is...

324
00:19:05,530 --> 00:19:09,430
It's just as you say, Kazuha.

325
00:19:11,430 --> 00:19:13,730
I can't...

326
00:19:13,730 --> 00:19:15,830
I can't stop my tears from falling.

327
00:19:25,090 --> 00:19:30,190
Did you really call the newspaper reporter, Mrs. Kawauchi here and stab her?

328
00:19:30,190 --> 00:19:33,690
Yes. I did it.

329
00:19:34,690 --> 00:19:37,290
I just can't believe it.

330
00:19:38,290 --> 00:19:41,590
Your deduction a year ago was fantastic.

331
00:19:41,590 --> 00:19:43,390
You saw through the trick in the wink of an eye

332
00:19:43,390 --> 00:19:47,790
and paved the way to solving the case with lightning speed.

333
00:19:47,790 --> 00:19:50,590
Why would a person like you, do something like this?

334
00:19:50,590 --> 00:19:52,390
You're over evaluating me.

335
00:19:53,590 --> 00:19:56,190
I'm not God.

336
00:19:56,190 --> 00:19:59,590
I hate people and make mistakes too.

337
00:20:00,590 --> 00:20:04,290
It seems that a year ago

338
00:20:04,290 --> 00:20:06,590
I wrongly made a culprit out of Mr. Hinohara

339
00:20:06,590 --> 00:20:08,990
who was innocent.

340
00:20:10,690 --> 00:20:14,990
Maybe you don't remember because you've lost your memory.

341
00:20:14,990 --> 00:20:17,190
But as far as that incident is concerned, there was legitimate evidence.

342
00:20:17,190 --> 00:20:18,390
Excuse me.

343
00:20:19,990 --> 00:20:21,890
The test results have been reached

344
00:20:21,890 --> 00:20:23,790
so I thought I'd report it.

345
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:24,890
Test results?

346
00:20:24,890 --> 00:20:27,990
That boy from Osaka asked me to get it.

347
00:20:29,090 --> 00:20:31,790
He asked me to check if the murder weapon knife

348
00:20:31,790 --> 00:20:35,290
and the piece of chain inside the lucky charm pouch that the boy had

349
00:20:35,290 --> 00:20:37,590
matched or not.

350
00:20:40,190 --> 00:20:41,790
And, what about the result?

351
00:20:41,790 --> 00:20:44,590
Just as you said, they didn't match.

352
00:20:44,590 --> 00:20:48,590
All right! It's just as I deduced!

353
00:20:48,590 --> 00:20:51,390
You mean that lucky charm, right?

354
00:20:51,390 --> 00:20:54,390
What does it have to with the knife?

355
00:20:54,390 --> 00:20:57,090
What on earth didn't match?

356
00:20:58,190 --> 00:21:01,690
It's what all humans are bestowed with

357
00:21:01,690 --> 00:21:03,590
from the heavens when they are born,

358
00:21:03,590 --> 00:21:06,590
an emblem that stays with you till the end of your lifetime.

359
00:21:10,290 --> 00:21:12,590
Since there is no one with the same,

360
00:21:12,590 --> 00:21:14,590
when it comes to criminal investigation,

361
00:21:14,590 --> 00:21:18,390
it is considered to be one of the most reliable evidence.

362
00:21:19,790 --> 00:21:22,190
Fingerprints, isn't it?

363
00:21:22,190 --> 00:21:23,190
Yes.

364
00:21:23,190 --> 00:21:26,590
Who is he?

365
00:21:26,590 --> 00:21:27,890
Death?

366
00:21:30,490 --> 00:21:31,990
Stand back.

367
00:21:35,490 --> 00:21:36,490
A gun?

368
00:21:36,490 --> 00:21:37,490
No use.

369
00:21:49,890 --> 00:21:51,690
Cut it out.

370
00:21:51,690 --> 00:21:54,890
Enough with the costume party already.

371
00:21:55,990 --> 00:21:57,790
Costume party?

372
00:21:57,790 --> 00:21:59,590
What're you talking about?

373
00:21:59,590 --> 00:22:03,690
Yes. If any trick was involved in this case

374
00:22:03,690 --> 00:22:05,990
it's his face.

375
00:22:05,990 --> 00:22:08,990
I mean it's unthinkable that the high school detective Shinichi Kudo

376
00:22:08,990 --> 00:22:11,790
would ever stab anybody.

377
00:22:13,190 --> 00:22:14,990
The first thing that bothered me was

378
00:22:14,990 --> 00:22:18,790
the attitude that Mouri's daughter took.

379
00:22:18,790 --> 00:22:21,590
Despite the Kudo she'd been waiting for all this time

380
00:22:21,590 --> 00:22:24,790
appearing before her,

381
00:22:24,790 --> 00:22:27,290
she acted as if she didn't know him and displayed a cold attitude.

382
00:22:27,290 --> 00:22:29,790
Normally, she would've clung to him and not let go, right?

383
00:22:31,090 --> 00:22:34,890
And the more so, if he has amnesia,

384
00:22:34,890 --> 00:22:38,890
at first I thought she was just hiding her embarrassment,

385
00:22:38,890 --> 00:22:41,690
but after I checked the hut of the culprit in the forest, I found out why!

386
00:22:41,690 --> 00:22:43,290
Culprit's hut?

387
00:22:43,290 --> 00:22:46,290
Yes, the pictures of Kudo that are pinned up on the wall

388
00:22:46,290 --> 00:22:48,390
were all slashed to pieces,

389
00:22:48,390 --> 00:22:50,590
and a great number of mirrors were cracked

390
00:22:50,590 --> 00:22:52,290
with the shattered pieces scattered over the floor.

391
00:22:52,290 --> 00:22:56,890
There could be only one reason that the guy who hates Kudo to the point

392
00:22:56,890 --> 00:23:00,890
of slashing his pictures would crack mirrors to pieces.

393
00:23:00,890 --> 00:23:05,690
He couldn't stand seeing the face of Kudo

394
00:23:05,690 --> 00:23:08,190
that was reflected in the mirror.

395
00:23:09,890 --> 00:23:11,890
Don't tell me that...

396
00:23:11,890 --> 00:23:16,190
Yes, he underwent plastic surgery

397
00:23:16,190 --> 00:23:19,590
and changed his face to that of this green-horn detective...

398
00:23:24,590 --> 00:23:27,390
stupid high school detective.

399
00:23:42,020 --> 00:23:44,020
Hey, this is...

400
00:23:44,020 --> 00:23:45,820
He's a perfect double.

401
00:23:47,820 --> 00:23:50,620
But, why would you change your face to Shinichi's?

402
00:23:50,620 --> 00:23:53,720
He called me out to that hut,

403
00:23:53,720 --> 00:23:55,920
confined me there and after becoming me,

404
00:23:55,920 --> 00:23:58,120
he was probably scheming to commit some sort of crime.

405
00:23:58,120 --> 00:24:01,120
His intention was to probably annihilate I, Shinichi Kudo...

406
00:24:01,120 --> 00:24:05,620
as a person, and from society too.

407
00:24:05,620 --> 00:24:08,820
Annihilate you?

408
00:24:08,820 --> 00:24:11,320
He pretended to have amnesia

409
00:24:11,320 --> 00:24:13,620
so that he wouldn't have to answer anything

410
00:24:13,620 --> 00:24:17,420
that my friends who he supposed would come along with me may ask.

411
00:24:17,420 --> 00:24:19,420
He went into the lake naked and had a hoarse voice

412
00:24:19,420 --> 00:24:22,520
as if having a cold for the same reason.

413
00:24:22,520 --> 00:24:24,120
Although he could make himself look like me,

414
00:24:24,120 --> 00:24:26,820
he couldn't copy my voice.

415
00:24:26,820 --> 00:24:30,820
Neither did he know what kind of clothes I would be wearing.

416
00:24:33,220 --> 00:24:37,720
Well, I too, when escaping from that hut fell into the lake,

417
00:24:37,720 --> 00:24:41,220
and have a bit of a hoarse voice with a cold.

418
00:24:41,220 --> 00:24:44,320
Then, the one who called the ambulance and police this morning

419
00:24:44,320 --> 00:24:46,520
-right after the incident was... -Me.

420
00:24:46,520 --> 00:24:50,620
I saw Mrs. Kawauchi and he come into this house,

421
00:24:50,620 --> 00:24:52,820
so I prepared for the worse.

422
00:24:52,820 --> 00:24:56,120
Then, why didn't you yourself rush inside and stop him?

423
00:24:56,120 --> 00:24:58,720
I couldn't even if I wanted to.

424
00:24:58,720 --> 00:25:00,620
Because when he came out of the house last night,

425
00:25:00,620 --> 00:25:03,320
from the protrusion in the back of his clothes,

426
00:25:03,320 --> 00:25:06,520
I was sure that he was armed with a gun.

427
00:25:06,520 --> 00:25:08,420
I guess it can't be helped.

428
00:25:08,420 --> 00:25:10,920
After all, "Failure means death"

429
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:13,520
was carved on the desk too.

430
00:25:13,520 --> 00:25:14,520
Yes.

431
00:25:14,520 --> 00:25:18,420
If he was ready to shoot a specific person,

432
00:25:18,420 --> 00:25:20,620
maybe I could've stopped him.

433
00:25:20,620 --> 00:25:23,320
If he had his mind made up to kill himself

434
00:25:23,320 --> 00:25:26,120
as soon as he found out that his scheme didn't work,

435
00:25:26,120 --> 00:25:29,720
the time I had to stop him was limited.

436
00:25:29,720 --> 00:25:32,920
That's why I took the bullets out of Officer Shiroyama's gun

437
00:25:32,920 --> 00:25:35,120
and scattered it before his eyes

438
00:25:35,120 --> 00:25:37,320
to make him hesitate and putting him off guard.

439
00:25:40,520 --> 00:25:43,320
Because he was probably planning to carry out his scheme

440
00:25:43,320 --> 00:25:45,720
as soon as I appeared before him.

441
00:25:46,720 --> 00:25:48,620
Isn't that right, Okuda?

442
00:25:48,620 --> 00:25:51,220
Rather, Makoto Hinohara?

443
00:25:56,420 --> 00:26:00,020
Makoto? You mean you're Makoto?

444
00:26:00,020 --> 00:26:01,220
He sure is.

445
00:26:01,220 --> 00:26:02,520
To do this much with plastic surgery

446
00:26:02,520 --> 00:26:04,520
would cost a lot of time and money.

447
00:26:04,520 --> 00:26:09,120
But, Makoto could do it because he got a lot of estate

448
00:26:09,120 --> 00:26:10,920
and his whereabouts were unknown for six months.

449
00:26:13,120 --> 00:26:19,320
If so, he would've hidden the gun in his own room in this house.

450
00:26:19,320 --> 00:26:21,120
He assumed beforehand that they would bring him back here

451
00:26:21,120 --> 00:26:24,120
to help him regain his memory.

452
00:26:24,120 --> 00:26:26,420
He then tells everyone that he wants to be alone,

453
00:26:26,420 --> 00:26:29,320
and that's when he retrieves the gun.

454
00:26:29,320 --> 00:26:34,020
But, why, why did he have to stab the newspaper reporter?

455
00:26:34,020 --> 00:26:36,120
He probably thought that she found out about everything

456
00:26:36,120 --> 00:26:38,520
because of her remark last night.

457
00:26:38,520 --> 00:26:41,220
Oh, my. What's with that look of yours?

458
00:26:41,220 --> 00:26:44,220
Don't tell me that you thought I didn't realize either?

459
00:26:45,220 --> 00:26:49,120
That you underwent plastic surgery to make yourself look like Kudo.

460
00:26:49,120 --> 00:26:51,020
But, I don't understand.

461
00:26:51,020 --> 00:26:53,920
When I came over to the house this morning,

462
00:26:53,920 --> 00:26:58,620
why didn't you say that you stabbed Mrs. Kawauchi?

463
00:26:58,620 --> 00:27:00,320
If you wanted to frame Kudo for the murder,

464
00:27:00,320 --> 00:27:02,720
wouldn't that have been faster?

465
00:27:06,920 --> 00:27:11,520
I was testing you detectives out.

466
00:27:12,520 --> 00:27:14,020
I wanted to see what kind of deduction

467
00:27:14,020 --> 00:27:17,820
you'd come up with after the evidence all pointed

468
00:27:17,820 --> 00:27:21,120
to Shinichi Kudo being the murderer.

469
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:28,120
Well, it seems they saw you through completely.

470
00:27:28,120 --> 00:27:31,520
Then, what about the incident that occurred a year ago?

471
00:27:31,520 --> 00:27:34,520
What's with Shinichi Kudo who made a stupid deduction

472
00:27:34,520 --> 00:27:36,920
saying that Mr. Hinohara committed forced double suicide

473
00:27:36,920 --> 00:27:41,020
when a robber made away with the valuables and murdered them?

474
00:27:41,020 --> 00:27:44,220
What about him?

475
00:27:48,620 --> 00:27:50,320
Kudo didn't make a mistake.

476
00:27:51,520 --> 00:27:53,320
That was a forced double suicide.

477
00:27:53,320 --> 00:27:54,420
What?

478
00:27:54,420 --> 00:27:56,520
The murder weapon of the killer,

479
00:27:56,520 --> 00:27:57,720
Mrs. Hinohara's jewelry,

480
00:27:57,720 --> 00:28:00,420
as well as her valuable Nioh statue were taken, you know?

481
00:28:00,420 --> 00:28:03,520
It's more than obvious that the killer took it with him.

482
00:28:03,520 --> 00:28:04,820
The lake...

483
00:28:05,920 --> 00:28:08,920
After Mr. Hinohara stabbed his wife,

484
00:28:08,920 --> 00:28:13,720
he sunk the murder weapon together with the jewelry into the lake.

485
00:28:13,720 --> 00:28:15,620
What're you talking about?

486
00:28:15,620 --> 00:28:19,620
It's close to 30 meters from this house to the lake.

487
00:28:19,620 --> 00:28:21,020
How would the culprit be able to take all that

488
00:28:21,020 --> 00:28:23,320
to the lake without leaving footprints behind?

489
00:28:23,320 --> 00:28:25,620
Not only the murder weapon and the jewelry,

490
00:28:25,620 --> 00:28:26,820
but the strings for the gold medals

491
00:28:26,820 --> 00:28:28,920
and the loops for quoits are also gone.

492
00:28:28,920 --> 00:28:30,920
Quoits?

493
00:28:30,920 --> 00:28:35,120
Mr. Hinohara's son Daiki was saying, remember?

494
00:28:35,120 --> 00:28:37,020
That his father was good at quoits

495
00:28:37,020 --> 00:28:39,820
and always played a perfect game, right?

496
00:28:39,820 --> 00:28:42,220
The scores that are written on the target of quoits

497
00:28:42,220 --> 00:28:44,820
are 10 points, 5 points, 2 points.

498
00:28:44,820 --> 00:28:46,720
So, if he wants to play a perfect game scoring 100 points,

499
00:28:46,720 --> 00:28:50,920
he needs 10 quoits, but there were only 9.

500
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:55,420
Besides, one pair of the Nioh statue was left untouched

501
00:28:55,420 --> 00:28:57,220
and taking into consideration

502
00:28:57,220 --> 00:29:01,220
that Mr. Hinohara used to be a player of field sports,

503
00:29:01,220 --> 00:29:02,820
the answer is obvious.

504
00:29:05,520 --> 00:29:07,220
Hammer throwing.

505
00:29:08,520 --> 00:29:10,620
He packed the Nioh statue that he used for weight together

506
00:29:10,620 --> 00:29:13,620
with the murder weapon, shoes and jewelry into a bag,

507
00:29:13,620 --> 00:29:15,220
and used the quoit as a handle

508
00:29:15,220 --> 00:29:19,120
by tying on the string of medal onto the package.

509
00:29:19,120 --> 00:29:22,220
He did this all to throw the bag into the lake from the veranda

510
00:29:22,220 --> 00:29:24,320
as he would do when hammer throwing.

511
00:29:24,320 --> 00:29:25,720
I see.

512
00:29:25,720 --> 00:29:28,220
He left one Nion statue behind

513
00:29:28,220 --> 00:29:31,320
because putting both in the bag would make it too heavy

514
00:29:31,320 --> 00:29:33,920
and the bag wouldn't reach the lake.

515
00:29:33,920 --> 00:29:35,520
Ridiculous.

516
00:29:35,520 --> 00:29:38,420
The bag would've never made it because of resistance from the wind.

517
00:29:38,420 --> 00:29:41,320
No, the bag made it.

518
00:29:41,320 --> 00:29:43,620
The bag, string and quoits

519
00:29:43,620 --> 00:29:46,520
have already been retrieved from the lake.

520
00:29:46,520 --> 00:29:50,020
Of course on the blade of the murder weapon knife,

521
00:29:50,020 --> 00:29:53,320
Mrs. Hinohara's blood was found and on the handle of the knife,

522
00:29:53,320 --> 00:29:55,620
Mr. Hinohara's fingerprints were found.

523
00:29:55,620 --> 00:29:58,620
There's no mistake that it was a forced double suicide

524
00:29:58,620 --> 00:30:00,020
committed by Mr. Hinohara.

525
00:30:01,120 --> 00:30:02,420
Not true.

526
00:30:02,420 --> 00:30:06,320
