794
00:43:53,070 --> 00:43:55,270
I'm no more than a driver.

795
00:43:55,270 --> 00:43:56,770
What about you people?

796
00:43:56,770 --> 00:43:59,870
Did you have any case to solve or something, Mr. Sleeping Kogoro?

797
00:44:00,870 --> 00:44:02,470
Yes. Well, sort of.

798
00:44:02,470 --> 00:44:06,170
Really? Well, excuse us, since we're in a rush.

799
00:44:06,170 --> 00:44:08,570
Tell us about the case some other day then!

800
00:44:10,370 --> 00:44:12,470
Since that incident is big news,

801
00:44:12,470 --> 00:44:13,970
as long as they read tomorrow's papers they'll find out about it

802
00:44:13,970 --> 00:44:15,070
without us telling them about it.

803
00:44:15,070 --> 00:44:18,170
No, I don't think it'll be in the papers.

804
00:44:19,370 --> 00:44:21,470
Nobody died as a result, and besides,

805
00:44:21,470 --> 00:44:23,670
the culprit is still a juvenile.

806
00:44:23,670 --> 00:44:26,370
Neither his name nor picture will be publicized.

807
00:44:26,370 --> 00:44:29,070
It seems that the newspaper reporter lady who was stabbed,

808
00:44:29,070 --> 00:44:31,870
also said that she won't write about it.

809
00:44:33,470 --> 00:44:36,270
You were sure lucky, Kudo.

810
00:44:42,370 --> 00:44:43,970
What's with that car?

811
00:44:43,970 --> 00:44:47,470
It's moving along scraping its body against the guardrail.

812
00:44:53,670 --> 00:44:54,970
Maybe he's sleeping at the wheels?

813
00:44:54,970 --> 00:44:56,870
If we leave it as is, there's sure to be a big accident.

814
00:45:05,670 --> 00:45:07,670
Hey, get up!

815
00:45:07,670 --> 00:45:09,270
Hey, you!

816
00:45:17,070 --> 00:45:19,470
Hey, something's not right.

817
00:45:19,470 --> 00:45:21,470
Get this car in front of that car.

818
00:45:21,470 --> 00:45:24,470
Hey! In front, don't tell me that...

819
00:45:28,170 --> 00:45:30,670
When you go up front slow down little by little.

820
00:45:30,670 --> 00:45:33,470
Idiot! If I do that, the rental car will...

821
00:45:33,470 --> 00:45:34,870
Never mind, just hurry.

822
00:45:57,370 --> 00:45:59,670
Gunpei? Gunpei?

823
00:45:59,670 --> 00:46:01,870
Hey, wait. Don't touch him.

824
00:46:01,870 --> 00:46:03,170
Please step back.

825
00:46:03,170 --> 00:46:04,770
Who're you people?

826
00:46:06,570 --> 00:46:09,770
-No good. -He's not breathing anymore.

827
00:46:10,970 --> 00:46:12,570
Look, Kudo.

828
00:46:12,570 --> 00:46:15,470
There's hemorrhaging under his eyes.

829
00:46:15,470 --> 00:46:18,070
Don't tell me that this is...

830
00:46:20,170 --> 00:46:22,770
a rope mark.

831
00:46:22,770 --> 00:46:24,970
Kudo, this is...

832
00:46:24,970 --> 00:46:26,570
Hey!

833
00:46:26,570 --> 00:46:27,970
What's wrong?

834
00:46:27,970 --> 00:46:31,070
Ran. There's a toll gate a kilometer from here.

835
00:46:31,070 --> 00:46:33,770
Call Officer Sato and have them block it off.

836
00:46:33,770 --> 00:46:35,170
Why?

837
00:46:35,170 --> 00:46:38,670
The driver of this car is dead.

838
00:46:38,670 --> 00:46:40,270
He was strangled.

839
00:46:42,070 --> 00:46:43,370
Strangled?

840
00:46:43,370 --> 00:46:44,770
Yes.

841
00:46:44,770 --> 00:46:49,770
In this moving car that's locked.

